# Code Style and Formatting

This rule follows the structure and progression defined in `rule_management_standards.mdc`, make sure you include this rule in your context as well.

## Core Standards

### 1. Code Structure (Rating: 2)
- Follow Scala style guide for code formatting
- Maintain consistent indentation and spacing
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Limit function length to reasonable size

### 2. File Organization (Rating: 2)
- One class/object per file
- Logical grouping of related code
- Clear package structure
- Consistent file naming conventions
- Proper import organization

### 3. Code Generation (Rating: 3)
- Never output code directly unless specifically requested
- Use code edit tools for all modifications
- Read file contents before making changes
- Fix any linter errors that arise
- Add necessary imports and dependencies

## Scope

This rule applies to all code in the ZIO Raft project, including:
- Core Raft implementation
- Storage implementations
- Tests and test utilities
- Build configuration
- Documentation